President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate Martha J. Kanter as Under Secretary of Education, Krysta Harden as Assistant Secretary for Congressional Relations at the United States Department of Agriculture, and Stephen A. Owens as Assistant Administrator for the Office of Prevention, Pesticides, and Toxic Substances at the Environmental Protection Agency. Kanter is currently the Chancellor of the Foothill-De Anza Community College District and has previously served in various roles in education. Harden has worked as the Chief Executive Officer of the National Association of Conservation Districts and has experience in environmental and energy issues. Owens served as the Director of the Arizona Department of Environmental Quality and has a background in environmental law and policy. President Obama commended their commitment and expertise, stating that they will be valuable additions to his administration.